{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/a-unified-model-for-text-mining-2085054f6072", "time": 1682996894.113903, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/a-unified-model-for-text-mining-2085054f6072/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "A General-Purpose Architecture for Text Mining | by Chris Thornton | Towards Data Science", "h1": "A General-Purpose Architecture for Text Mining", "description": "Natural Language Processing (NLP) is an exciting emerging field in the sphere of Artificial Intelligence. Major evolution in linguistic and machine learning algorithms make the sub-tasks needed for\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "http://web.eecs.umich.edu/~mihalcea/papers/mihalcea.emnlp04.pdf", "anchor_text": "TextRank", "paragraph_index": 8}, {"url": "https://nlp.stanford.edu/pubs/glove.pdf", "anchor_text": "GloVe word embeddings", "paragraph_index": 11}, {"url": "https://www.nltk.org/book/", "anchor_text": "Natural Language Tool-Kit (NLTK) book", "paragraph_index": 15}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/christopher-thornton1", "anchor_text": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/christopher-thornton1", "paragraph_index": 17}], "all_paragraphs": ["Natural Language Processing (NLP) is an exciting emerging field in the sphere of Artificial Intelligence. Major evolution in linguistic and machine learning algorithms make the sub-tasks needed for computers to process and analyze large amounts of natural language data viable. Research has shown that computers are capable of carrying out tasks thought to be solely possible by humans.", "Broader NLP tasks such as Information Extraction (IE) require the arrangement of sub-tasks architected with flexibility in mind. The discussed architecture possesses two important advantages over most IE systems, namely that it is general-purpose and domain independent.", "The initial handling of textual data calls for a pipeline of steps sequenced to provide processed input to our models. Text is first tokenized or segmented into words, punctuation marks, etc.", "Each Token is tagged with morphological, grammatical, and alphanumeric features. Additional features such as stems, syntactic dependency labels, start and end indices may apply to your use case.", "Machine learning models use statistical inference to automatically determine morphological and syntactical features through the analysis of large corpora of typical real-world documents. These statistical inferences are used in tandem with hand-coded heuristics for best results.", "A Named Entity Recognition (NER) model will selected terms into predefined buckets: A person, organization, event, place, etc.", "The terms are NOT compared with a list of elements for each set, part of the reason why ML techniques are so successful is that they find statistical patterns that lack explainability but work in practice.", "Domain-dependent dictionary lookup methods require routine maintenance due to more/fewer elements in sets over time and not consider context.", "Keyterms are extracted using TextRank; a graph-based ranking model.", "In short, a graph is constructed where distinct nouns, verbs and adjectives from our text serve as a vertex. Edges are created if lexical units co-occur (appear together within a fixed window of words).", "To rank words: initialize all the vertices to one, collect the influence of each of its inbound connections, iterate until convergence, and normalize the score.", "The system becomes domain-independent with the use of pre-trained word vectors; wherein words of interest are mapped to vectors of real numbers. GloVe word embeddings are created by aggregating global word-word co-occurrence matrices from a large corpus. The cosine distance between GloVe vectors conveniently indicate semantic similarity.", "Among the many clustering methods available, Overlapping Partitioning Clustering is preferable as it allows for a word to fit into multiple categories simultaneously. The intuition for using this method is that fuzziness often exists between categories in natural language.", "Cluster labels will be chosen from a controlled vocabulary of words and phrases. Bayesian inference from keyterm context vectors is more likely to yield an accurate label than naive cosine similarity.", "The extracted information can be used for many downstream tasks including text summarization, event extraction, conceptual mapping and relation extraction.", "If you\u2019re interested in learning more about NLP, I highly recommend reading the Natural Language Tool-Kit (NLTK) book.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Sharing ideas and research about ML, NLP, Data Science | Toronto, Canada | https://www.linkedin.com/in/christopher-thornton1"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F2085054f6072&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fa-unified-model-for-text-mining-2085054f6072&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fa-unified-model-for-text-mining-2085054f6072&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}